                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d165">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3801b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Great Britain (<persName corresp="#p_AR1" type="to"
                            >Atherton</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-31T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 31, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. Inform Prime Minister immediately that I have taken up with the President the
                    matter discussed between him and me by telephone this morning and last evening.
                    We feel that for the moment the project should be postponed. I shall probably
                    later renew conference with regard to it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
